OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773774690
OL,3,CHolyrood set for knife-edge vote on
OL,4,Cwhether to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FThe Isle of Man and Jersey have
OL,7,Falready passed legislation to legalise
OL,8,Fassisted dying, ITV News UK Editor
OL,9,FPaul Brand reports
OL,11,FMSPs in Scotland are set to decide
OL,12,Fwhether to legalise assisted dying on
OL,13,FTuesday, in a historic knife-edge vote.
OL,15,FLiam McArthur, who tabled the Assisted
OL,16,FDying for Terminally Ill Adults
OL,17,F(Scotland) Bill, has made last-minute
OL,18,Fpleas to MSPs to pass the legislation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773774690
OL,3,CHolyrood set for knife-edge vote on
OL,4,Cwhether to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FHe has insisted the proposals would be
OL,7,F"the toughest and most comprehensively
OL,8,Fsafeguarded assisted dying Bill in the
OL,9,Fworld".
OL,11,FThe Bill will go through its stage
OL,12,Fthree vote in the Scottish Parliament
OL,13,Fat about 10 pm on Tuesday.
OL,15,FA close result is expected. All MSPs
OL,16,Fare being given a free vote rather
OL,17,Fthan being whipped along party lines.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773774690
OL,3,CHolyrood set for knife-edge vote on
OL,4,Cwhether to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FAs supporters of assisted dying
OL,7,Fgathered in the morning, McArthur said
OL,8,Fthat voting down the Bill would leave
OL,9,Fterminally ill Scots "more at risk,
OL,10,Fmore isolated and more vulnerable".
OL,12,FHe told the Press Association: "I just
OL,13,Fhope my MSP colleagues grasp this
OL,14,Fopportunity to address a failing in
OL,15,Fthe current law ` the ban on assisted
OL,16,Fdying, which is leaving a small but
OL,17,Fnot insignificant number of dying
OL,18,FScots and their families horrendous
OL,19,Fdecisions".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773774690
OL,3,CHolyrood set for knife-edge vote on
OL,4,Cwhether to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FSome MSPs are still uncertain about
OL,7,Fhow they will vote on Tuesday evening,
OL,8,Fhe said.
OL,10,FOpponents of the legislation, who fear
OL,11,Fthe impact of assisted dying on the
OL,12,Fdisabled and other vulnerable groups,
OL,13,Fwill also be gathering outside the
OL,14,FScottish Parliament in advance of the
OL,15,Fvote.
OL,17,FThe vote comes after the Isle of Man
OL,18,Fand Jersey have already passed
OL,19,Flegislation to legalise assisted dying.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773774690
OL,3,CHolyrood set for knife-edge vote on
OL,4,Cwhether to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FIn Wales, the Senedd backed a
OL,7,FLegislative Consent Motion (LCM),
OL,8,Fwhich means the service could one day
OL,9,Fbe made available on the NHS in Wales.
OL,11,FHowever, the decision to change the
OL,12,Flaw on assisted dying in Wales still
OL,13,Fremains in Westminster.
OL,15,FMeanwhile, more than 100 Labour MPs
OL,16,Fhave written to the prime minister
OL,17,Fasking him to stop peers from
OL,18,Fpurposefully blocking the passage of
OL,19,Fthe assisted dying Bill.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773774690
OL,3,CHolyrood set for knife-edge vote on
OL,4,Cwhether to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FIn total, over 150 MPs have signed the
OL,7,Fprivate letter addressed to Starmer,
OL,8,Fincluding parliamentarians from the
OL,9,FConservatives, Liberal Democrats,
OL,10,FGreens, Plaid Cymru, and Reform UK.
OL,12,FThey have raised concerns about the
OL,13,Fslow progress of the Terminally Ill
OL,14,FAdults (End of Life) Bill through the
OL,15,FHouse of Lords, with only half of the
OL,16,F1,200 amendments up for consideration
OL,17,Fhaving been debated after 11 days of
OL,18,Fscrutiny.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
