PN,30907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773774690
OL,3,CHolyrood set for knife-edge vote on
OL,4,Cwhether to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FLast week, MSPs made changes to the
OL,7,FAssisted Dying for Terminally Ill
OL,8,FAdults (Scotland) Bill in four lengthy
OL,9,Fsessions at Holyrood, with a total of
OL,10,F175 changes to the legislation agreed.
OL,12,FMcArthur's proposals would allow Scots
OL,13,Fto legally seek help to end their
OL,14,Flife, with the Bill requiring two
OL,15,Fdoctors to confirm that a person is
OL,16,Fterminally ill and has the mental
OL,17,Fcapacity to make such a request.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,310,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1773774690
OL,3,CHolyrood set for knife-edge vote on
OL,4,Cwhether to legalise assisted dying
OL,6,FMeanwhile, a change introduced last
OL,7,Fweek would mean that people should be
OL,8,F"reasonably expected" to have six
OL,9,Fmonths to live or less before they
OL,10,Fwould be eligible for an assisted
OL,11,Fdeath.
OL,13,FThis is the third time MSPs have
OL,14,Fconsidered legislation on assisted
OL,15,Fdying, with two previous attempts
OL,16,Fhaving failed at their first vote.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
